criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
1. Age ≥18 years old;
2. Acue ischemic stroke;
3. NIHSS ≥ 4 at enrollment;
4. Intracranial large artery occlusion including: internal carotid artery (T/L), middle cerebral artery (M1/M2),anterior cerebral artery (A1/A2), basilar artery, vertebral artery (V4), posterior cerebral artery (P1);
5. ASPECT (anterior circulation) or PC-ASPECT (posterior circulation) ≥ 6;
6. Planned to receive endovascular treatment, including intra-arterial thrombolysis, thrombectomy, and angioplasty (onset-to-puncture time less than 8 hours in the anterior circulation and less than 12 hours in the posterior circulation were suggested)
7. The patient or relative give written informed consent.
Exclusion Criteria:
1. modified Rankin Scale (mRS) >2 before the event;
2. ASPECTS (anterior circulation) or PC-ASPECTS (posterior circulation) <6, or
3. Diagnosis of intracranial hemorrhagic disease, such as intracranial hemorrhage, subarachnoid hemorrhage and so on.
4. History of coagulation dysfunction, systemic bleeding, neutropenia or thrombocytopenia.
5. History of kidney dysfunction, elevating serum creatinine (> 2 times normal upper limit).
6. History of severe cardio-pulmonary diseases which is not suitable for this study judged by investigator.
7. Severe non-cardiovascular comorbidity with life expectancy < 3 months or failed to follow the study for other reasons.
8. Contraindications for the digital subtraction angiography procedure, including severe allergy for contrast agent with or without Iodine.
9. Pregnancy or lactation, and women of childbearing age not practicing reliable contraception who do not have a documented negative pregnancy test.
10. Incapable to follow this study for mental illness, cognitive or emotional disorder.
11. Unsuitable for this study in the opinion of the investigators.
